---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const collections=[
  {eyebrow:'Wear',title:'Wearable symbols',copy:'Bracelets, necklaces, pendants, scarves and small adornments shaped as daily reminders of courage, clarity, compassion and return.',link:'/spiritual-jewelry/',label:'Explore jewelry guides'},
  {eyebrow:'Place',title:'Objects for your space',copy:'Incense vessels, tea and table objects, small altars, printed imagery and material pieces that make a room feel more intentional.',link:'/symbols/',label:'Explore symbols'},
  {eyebrow:'Practice',title:'Objects for reflection',copy:'Journals, cards, prompts, meditation stones and quiet study objects for moments when you want to listen more closely.',link:'/practices/',label:'Explore practices'},
  {eyebrow:'Carry',title:'Objects for the road',copy:'Pouches, travel textiles, notebooks and small companions for thresholds, journeys and the next chapter.',link:'/paths/',label:'Choose a path'}
];
---
<Base title="Shop Dunhuang Within | Objects of Intention" description="Shop future Dunhuang Within objects of intention: jewelry, ritual and home objects, reflection tools, textiles and travel companions inspired by Dunhuang culture.">
  <section class="object-hero"><div class="wrap"><p class="eyebrow">Shop Dunhuang Within</p><h1>Objects for the energy you choose to carry.</h1><p class="lede">Jewelry, ritual objects, paper goods, textiles and quiet tools shaped by Dunhuang’s cultural memory—for wearing, placing, carrying and returning to what matters.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="#collections">Explore the shop</a><a class="button secondary" href="/find-your-path/">Find your path</a></div></div></section>
  <article class="article object-story">
    <p class="eyebrow">Culture before claim</p><h2>Energy is a relationship, not a promise.</h2><p>For Dunhuang Within, “energy” names the shift that can happen when a material, image or ritual brings you back to attention. We begin with a documented mural, manuscript, landscape or symbol; name the cultural source; then describe our contemporary interpretation. The object does not do the inner work for you. Touch, repetition and attention help you remember the work you chose.</p>
    <figure class="material-reference"><img src="/images/dunhuang/wood-buddhist-carving.jpg" alt="Dense wall of carved wooden Buddhist figures used as a material and devotional art reference" width="1366" height="2048" loading="lazy" decoding="async" /><figcaption>A wooden Buddhist carving reference from outside the Mogao Caves. It is included for material study, not labeled as a Dunhuang artifact.</figcaption></figure>
    <div class="carry-flow"><span>Historical source</span><span>Material or symbol</span><span>Personal intention</span><span>Daily practice</span><span>Object</span></div>
    <h2 id="collections">A shop for every way you return.</h2>
    <div class="collection-grid">{collections.map(item=><section><p class="eyebrow">{item.eyebrow}</p><h3>{item.title}</h3><p>{item.copy}</p><a href={item.link}>{item.label} →</a></section>)}</div>
    <h2>Four paths. Many forms.</h2>
    <div class="collection-grid"><section><p class="eyebrow">Courage</p><h3>Desert Crossing</h3><p>Warm mineral tones, grounding objects and practical companions for the moment between an ending and a beginning.</p><a href="/paths/#desert-crossing">Enter the path →</a></section><section><p class="eyebrow">Clarity</p><h3>Hidden Cave</h3><p>Reflective stones, paper objects and quiet forms inspired by inner listening and what waits to be read.</p><a href="/paths/#hidden-cave">Enter the path →</a></section><section><p class="eyebrow">Renewal</p><h3>Oasis Return</h3><p>Water and green tones, restorative room objects and tactile reminders of enoughness.</p><a href="/paths/#oasis-return">Enter the path →</a></section><section><p class="eyebrow">Direction</p><h3>Silk Road</h3><p>Layered forms, route-inspired objects and travel companions for connection and choosing without certainty.</p><a href="/paths/#silk-road">Enter the path →</a></section></div>
    <h2>Explore meaning before choosing an object.</h2>
    <ul><li><a href="/places/dunhuang/spiritual-jewelry/">Dunhuang jewelry: culture, symbols and intention</a></li><li><a href="/places/dunhuang/dunhuang-lotus-symbol/">Dunhuang lotus symbol: art and a modern practice</a></li><li><a href="/places/dunhuang/protection-symbols-dunhuang-art/">Protection symbols in Dunhuang art</a></li><li><a href="/places/dunhuang/buddhist-jewelry-meaning/">Buddhist jewelry meaning: context before a symbol</a></li><li><a href="/places/dunhuang/dunhuang-mandala-meaning/">Dunhuang mandala meaning: order and attention</a></li><li><a href="/places/dunhuang/feitian-spiritual-meaning/">The spiritual meaning of Dunhuang Feitian</a></li><li><a href="/places/dunhuang/lotus-jewelry-meaning/">Lotus jewelry meaning in Buddhist art</a></li><li><a href="/places/dunhuang/crystal-bracelet-intention/">How to choose a crystal bracelet by intention</a></li></ul>
    <h2>Our promise</h2><p>Every future object will state its materials, maker, cultural source and contemporary intention. We will not claim that an object treats disease, guarantees fortune, contains measurable “Dunhuang energy,” or has been blessed when no documented blessing took place.</p>
    <div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/find-your-path/">Find Your Path</a><a class="button secondary" href="/symbols/">Explore Dunhuang Symbols</a></div>
  </article>
</Base>
<style>.object-hero{min-height:78vh;display:flex;align-items:end;padding:10rem 0 6rem;color:var(--moonlight);background:linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(16,17,13,.96),rgba(16,17,13,.45)),url('/images/dunhuang/cave-buddha.jpg') center/cover}.object-hero h1{max-width:900px}.object-story{padding-top:6rem}.material-reference{display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(0,1fr) 14rem;gap:1.5rem;align-items:end;margin:4rem 0}.material-reference img{width:100%;max-height:720px;object-fit:cover;object-position:center 42%}.material-reference figcaption{font-size:.72rem;color:var(--ink-muted)}.carry-flow{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);margin:3rem 0 6rem;border-block:1px solid var(--line)}.carry-flow span{padding:1.2rem .5rem;border-right:1px solid var(--line);font-size:.7rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.1em}.collection-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;margin:2rem 0 6rem;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}.collection-grid section{padding:2.5rem;border-right:1px solid var(--line);border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}@media(max-width:700px){.object-hero{min-height:70vh;padding:8rem 0 4rem}.material-reference{grid-template-columns:1fr}.material-reference img{max-height:620px}.carry-flow,.collection-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.carry-flow span{border-right:0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}.collection-grid section{padding:2rem 0;border-right:0}}</style>
